Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle rising to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Agesilochos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0037.01, where the end of line 2 is also worn.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (160)
